Task: Phase 2 - Init Autoload Registration (Prepend + Auto-fix)

Summary: Rewrote register_coverage_autoload() to prepend _GDTCoverage as
the first entry in [autoload] instead of appending. Added auto-fix logic
that detects when _GDTCoverage exists but is not in position 0, moves it
to position 0, and prints a warning to stderr. This ensures
_GDTCoverage._ready() runs before any other autoload creates script
instances, so instrumentation via reload() succeeds.

Files modified:
- src/gd_tools/init.py: Rewrote register_coverage_autoload() (lines 345-435)
- tests/unit/test_init.py: Added 4 new tests (prepend, move-to-first,
  warns-when-moving, no-warning-when-already-first)

Test results: 9 register_coverage_autoload tests pass, 648 total unit
tests pass. Coverage on init.py: 98% line, 95% branch.

Why: Autoload ordering is critical. _GDTCoverage must be first so its
_ready() can instrument scripts before any other autoload creates
instances. reload() fails with ERR_ALREADY_IN_USE when active instances
exist.
